FuncDef: The reset conflict-ip-address command identifies one IP address or a segment of IP addresses as available during IP address conflict removal.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the start IP address of a conflict IP address segment.
The value is in dotted decimal notation.

Specifies the end IP address of a conflict IP address segment.
The value is in dotted decimal notation.

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
The reset conflict-ip-address command identifies one IP address or a segment of IP addresses as available during IP address conflict removal.
